label.value: adult antennal lobe local neuron TC-LN

value.value: Adult local neuron of the antennal lobe that develops from neuroblast ALv2 (Schlegel et al., 2021) and has its soma ventral to the antennal lobe (Chou et al., 2022). It is unilateral and it has a sparse arborization pattern (Schlegel et al., 2021). It innervates antennal lobe glomeruli DA1, DC3, DL3, DL4, VA1d and VA1v (Chou et al., 2022). Other glomeruli innervated can vary between individuals or within the same individual under different conditions (Chou et al., 2022). Its presynapses are evenly distributed along its processes (Chou et al., 2022). It receives input mainly from olfactory receptor neurons and sends output to uniglomerular projection neurons, but its connectivity pattern can vary in each glomerulus (Chou et al., 2022). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Chou et al., 2022). It is glutamatergic (Chou et al., 2022).

definition.value: Chou et al. (2022) say name is due to innervation of glomeruli targeted by trichoid ORNs (DA1, DL3, Va1d, Va1v), but are not explicit about what 'TC-LN' stands for.

label.value: adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron type 3 adPN

value.value: Adult brain-intrinsic neuron with its soma in the brain, ventral to the antennal lobe (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It belongs to the ALad1 hemilineage (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has postsynapses in the ipsilateral antennal lobe (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has presynapses in the ipsilateral posterior lateral protocerebrum, the ipsilateral superior clamp, the ipsilateral antennal lobe, the ipsilateral lateral horn and the ipsilateral inferior clamp (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron type 4 adPN

value.value: Adult multiglomerular antennal lobe projection neuron belonging to group 4 (Scheffer et al., 2020). It develops from neuroblast ALad1 and follows the medial antennal lobe tract (Bates et al., 2020; Scheffer et al., 2020). It has postsynaptic sites in the mushroom body, antennal lobe glomerulus VC1, antennal lobe glomerulus VC3, antennal lobe glomerulus VM4, medial antennal lobe tract, lateral horn, antennal lobe glomerulus VC5, antennal lobe glomerulus VC4, calyx of mushroom body, antennal lobe and antennal lobe glomerulus VM6 (Scheffer et al., 2020). It has presynaptic sites in the mushroom body, lateral horn, calyx of mushroom body and antennal lobe (Scheffer et al., 2020).
